          </td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <p><b>To order publications:</b> <br>
        <br>
        Contact the  <a href="http://www.ncjrs.org"><strong>National 
        Criminal Justice Reference Service (NCJRS)</strong></a>.</p>
      <p> 
      <ul>
        <LI><STRONG>Order online</STRONG><BR>
          If you have a forms-compatible browser, you can place your order directly 
          through the Internet at the <A HREF="http://www.ncjrs.org/statordr.html"><STRONG>Online 
          Order Form</STRONG></A>.<br><br>    </li> 
      
        <li><strong>Order by telephone</strong><br>
          In the United States, the NCJRS Clearinghouse offers toll-free access 
          at <strong>800-851-3420.</strong><br>
          <br>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Order by FAX</strong><br>
          FAX your order to the clearinghouse at <strong>301-519-5212</strong>. 
          Include your name, address, and telephone number along with the title 
          and NCJ number of the reports you desire.</li>
      </ul>
      <p><b>To obtain datasets and codebooks:</b> 
      <ul>
        <li><b>Download online</b><br>
          <A HREF="http://www.icpsr.umich.edu/NACJD/index.html"> <STRONG>National 
          Archive of Criminal Justice Data</STRONG></A> of the Inter-university 
          Consortium of Political and Social Research at the University of Michigan<br>
          <br>
         </li>
        <li><STRONG>Request 
          by phone or in writing</STRONG></li>
    
      <DL>
        <DD>National Archive 
          of Criminal Justice Data <BR>
          ICPSR<BR>
          Institute for Social Research<BR>
          <GEO TYPE="US">P.O. Box 1248<BR>
          Ann Arbor, MI 48106<BR>
          USA</GEO><BR>
          1-800-999-0960<BR>
          1-734-998-9825 
      </DL>  </ul>
    </td>
  </TR>



